<br>
If you want to stick with MS products, I suggest going to www.tucows.com or www.jumbo.com.  I find both have tons of software from freeware to commercial.  Tucows has a couple Mail Servers listed for under $50, and I didn't scroll through the whole list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#778899>(12/11/01 3:00:50 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.roneymis.com/images/Aejis.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Freeware Servers</span><hr size=1> search for wu-ftp.  It's open source, avail for Un*x and Win as well.  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.landfield.com/wu-ftpd/">www.landfield.com/wu-ftpd/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> might have the right link for ya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uaoxmodeus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aoxmodeus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#778899>(12/11/01 3:05:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Freeware Servers</span><hr size=1> For NT, you can use IIS as your ftp server.  <br>
<br>
It's built in...  just needs to have the right service installed and configured.<br>
<br>
For email, you may want to check out a little program called &quot;NTMail&quot;.. it's VERY basic.  Do a search on Tucows or download.com and you should come up with it. <br>
